This paper discusses a method for efficient search and learning using hashing techniques. The focus is on large-scale linear learning and sublinear time near-neighbor search, which are topics typically covered in the machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of sparse datasets, which is a common theme in the data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of probability analysis and experiments to validate the method, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
